    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen rebinding 'i' in visual mode, neovim seems to get stuck between the regular 'i' function and whatever it was bound to, waiting for a second key press before executing.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUse the following config options:\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('v', 'i', 'k')\nvim.keymap.set('v', 'k', 'i')\n```\nGo into visual mode and try to use the new 'i' binding a few times.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should move cursor up in this instance, but it does nothing on first press.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim does not offer lua config, but to my knowledeg\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot version: 1.26.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nArch official package",
